                    <span>This book is always at arm's reach in my office. It is written in plain English, so that you don't have to be an advertising executive to put Kathy's methods to work. It takes a lot of the fear and mystery out of advertising and guides you step-by-step. Furthermore, Kathy is obviously well versed in all typres of media (TV, Radio, Outdoor, etc.) which is not always the case. This is helpful for the small business owner as he/she may not be able to afford TV but can afford Direct Mail. If you are unsure about any kind of advertising on the local level, this book is a must. You really will come away feeling confident that you can put together a successful advertising plan. I wish I had this book ten years ago when I was starting out. I would have had a working knowledge of advertising that employed common sense.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">This book will give you the edge over your competitor.</div>
